.cs 3 on
.item 'SHOW GROUP Command' 'Added on 09/18/80 by EAB'
.boxon
SHOW GROUP [collect-options]
.*         <--------------->
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP SHOW GROUP collect-options
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The SHOW GROUP command displays the current value of ACCOUNT (i.e., the user
and group codes), as well as the logged-on ACCOUNT.  Note that all charges for
the session are incurred by the logged-on user regardless of the value of
ACCOUNT.

SHOW ACCOUNT and SHOW USER also display the current value of account.

.* SELECT 'SHOW GROUP Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION COLLECT-OPTIONS,BY,KEEP,NOCLEAR,NOCLR,CLEAR,CLR,WARN,NOWARN
.optix collect-options
collect-options\allow you to insert the system response to the SHOW GROUP
                command into your active file.  Type HELP COLLECT-OPTIONS for
                a description of these options.
.cs 3 off
